    "result": {"data":{"markdownRemark":{"excerpt":"Hi Friends üëã, Welcome To aGuideHub!  To make mui avatar with name in React js, you can use this code . It will make mui avatar with name in react js. Today, I‚Ä¶","html":"<p>Hi Friends üëã,</p>\n<p>Welcome To aGuideHub! </p>\n<p>To make mui avatar with name in React js, you can use this code <code class=\"language-text\">&lt;Typography></code>. It will make mui avatar with name in react js.</p>\n<p>Today, I am going to show you, how to make mui avatar with name in react js.</p>\n<h2>Installation</h2>\n<p>Install the following packages to use mui avatar in react js.</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">npm</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">npm install @mui<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>material @emotion<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>react @emotion<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>styled</code></pre></div>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">yarn</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">yarn add @mui<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>material @emotion<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>react @emotion<span class=\"token operator\">/</span>styled</code></pre></div>\n<p>Table of contents</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Install MUI and create a new React app.</li>\n<li>Import the Avatar component from MUI.</li>\n<li>Use the Avatar component in your JS code.</li>\n<li>Add inline styles to adjust the name.</li>\n</ul>\n<h3>Step 1: Install MUI and create a new React app.</h3>\n<p>First you have to install the React project. You should use <code class=\"language-text\">create-react-app</code> command to create a new React project.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\">npx create<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>react<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app my<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app\ncd my<span class=\"token operator\">-</span>app\nnpm start</code></pre></div>\n<h3>Step 2: Import the Avatar component from MUI.</h3>\n<p>After installing <code class=\"language-text\">MUI</code>, you have to import your React component. To do this, add the following line to the top of your component file.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> Avatar<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> Typography <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'@mui/material'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<h3>Step 3: Use the Avatar component in your JS code.</h3>\n<p>You can use the <code class=\"language-text\">Avatar</code> component in your react js. For example, you can have the following code to display an avatar with an <code class=\"language-text\">image</code>.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>Avatar src<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"/path/to/image.jpg\"</span> <span class=\"token operator\">/</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span></code></pre></div>\n<h3>Step 4: Add inline styles to adjust the name.</h3>\n<p>You can add inline styles to the Typography component. For example, you can add the following style to set the <code class=\"language-text\">ml</code> to <code class=\"language-text\">1</code> pixels.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>Typography variant<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"subtitle1\"</span> sx<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> <span class=\"token literal-property property\">ml</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token number\">1</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    John Doe\n<span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>Typography<span class=\"token operator\">></span></code></pre></div>\n<h2>MUI material make mui avatar name example.</h2>\n<p>The below code is an example of making name of mui avatar using.\nThe <code class=\"language-text\">Avatar</code> component is used to display an image of a person. The <code class=\"language-text\">typography</code> component has been used to display the person‚Äôs name. The <code class=\"language-text\">margin-left</code> has been given with the help of <code class=\"language-text\">sx</code> prop for the space between avatar and name.</p>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">App.js</code></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"js\"><pre class=\"language-js\"><code class=\"language-js\"><span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> React <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'react'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">import</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> Avatar<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> Typography <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">from</span> <span class=\"token string\">'@mui/material'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">const</span> <span class=\"token function-variable function\">App</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token operator\">=></span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">return</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>div style<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> <span class=\"token literal-property property\">display</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'flex'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token literal-property property\">alignItems</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token string\">'center'</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>Avatar src<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"/path/to/image.jpg\"</span> <span class=\"token operator\">/</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span>Typography variant<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token string\">\"subtitle1\"</span> sx<span class=\"token operator\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span> <span class=\"token literal-property property\">ml</span><span class=\"token operator\">:</span> <span class=\"token number\">1</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n        John Doe\n      <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>Typography<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n    <span class=\"token operator\">&lt;</span><span class=\"token operator\">/</span>div<span class=\"token operator\">></span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">export</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">default</span> App<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<p>In the above code example, I have used the <code class=\"language-text\">@mui/material</code> component and made mui avatar with name in react js.</p>\n<p>Check the output of the above code example.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 269px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/58934b5b4fda0f2bcedb838cc6b2d671/9fef4/avatar-with-name.webp\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 62.0253164556962%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/webp;base64,UklGRloAAABXRUJQVlA4IE4AAADQAwCdASoUAAwAPtFUpEuoJKOhsAgBABoJQBOj+ABgab/sffDSSwAAy0/As77Ik23DYF/DT8xRMDguW8kjgPFZOeIGhk3ajDdhRwQAAAA='); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"React, Mui, avatar\"\n        title=\"React, Mui, avatar\"\n        src=\"/static/58934b5b4fda0f2bcedb838cc6b2d671/9fef4/avatar-with-name.webp\"\n        srcset=\"/static/58934b5b4fda0f2bcedb838cc6b2d671/81b7c/avatar-with-name.webp 158w,\n/static/58934b5b4fda0f2bcedb838cc6b2d671/9fef4/avatar-with-name.webp 269w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 269px) 100vw, 269px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Here, we are provided code sandbox links for the above program make mui avatar with name in react js. Then you can use whenever you want and do the changes as per your requirements.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://aguidehub.com/codesandbox/?code=jolly-pond-wfz10d\" rel=\"nofollow\"  target=\"_BLANK\" >Try it Yourself</a></p>\n<p>All the best üëç</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"How to make mui avatar with name in react js?","tags":["React"],"date":"April 20, 2023","description":"Example of make mui avatar with name in React js with step by step tutorial - aGuideHub","social_image":"media/template/reactjs.jpg"}},"prev":{"frontmatter":{"title":"How to make mui avatar with tooltip in react js?"},"fields":{"slug":"/blog/2023-04-20-how-to-make-mui-avatar-with-tooltip-in-react-js/"}},"next":{"frontmatter":{"title":"How to make mui avatar with shadow in react js?"},"fields":{"slug":"/blog/2023-04-19-how-to-make-mui-avatar-with-shadow-in-react-js/"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/blog/2023-04-20-how-to-make-mui-avatar-with-name-in-react-js/","prevSlug":"/blog/2023-04-20-how-to-make-mui-avatar-with-tooltip-in-react-js/","nextSlug":"/blog/2023-04-19-how-to-make-mui-avatar-with-shadow-in-react-js/"}},
